column1:
NM = Not Meaningful due to large relative standard error.
Note: Data is reported as collected. All Technologies does not include photovoltaic storage.
Adjustments add capacity for non-respondents and remove capacity lost in conversion from DC to AC. The adjusted capacity values reported in the adjustments are for net metering and virtual net metering < 1 MW combined.
Some utilities reclassified net metering as non net metering distributed, or vice versa.
Source: U.S. Energy Information Administration, Form EIA-861M, 'Monthly Electric Power Industry Report.'
